# ── Realtime: pick ONE path (checked in this priority order) ─────────────────

# (A) SUPABASE REALTIME — recommended for a hosted, always-on live link with
#     zero server of your own. Live edits/cursors ride Supabase "broadcast";
#     a Postgres snapshot (supabase/schema.sql) keeps rooms durable offline.
#     The anon key is public/client-safe.
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOURPROJECT.supabase.co
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJ...your-anon-public-key...

# (B) Self-hosted y-websocket (e.g. Docker on the Hetzner box, behind Caddy TLS)
# VITE_SYNC_WS_URL=wss://bar-sync.yourdomain.com

# (C) Combined server (server/server.mjs) serving the app + websocket on one
#     origin (used for the ngrok build). Derives wss:// from the page origin.
# VITE_SYNC_SAME_ORIGIN=1

# If NONE are set → LOCAL mode: instant boot, IndexedDB persistence, same-browser
# tabs sync. Single-device only.
